    <item>
      <title>Hero of the Kingdom Armor Set</title>
      <author>khazmo</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/612870</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/612870#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">76ad06c06b76d61a35abda0270424c4524b6329f</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 10 Aug 2025 06:55:46 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6898406f637b6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68984076f179f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6898407e998d2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6898408887d61.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;Should work on Zelda ToTK versions 1.0 through 1.2.1 (will look into getting some of the more recent updates soon but I have not yet done these on my own copy as of yet).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod adds a standalone armor set to Zelda Tears of the Kingdom. The locations for each of the parts are as follows:&lt;br&gt;1. Upper Armor - Zelda's Well in Hateno Village&lt;br&gt;2. Lower Armor - Small cottage near Fort Hateno&lt;br&gt;3. Cap &amp;amp; Head Armor - Very top of Castle Hyrule&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The armor set stats are as follows:&lt;br&gt;Upper Armor - 20 Armor, Resist Hot &amp;amp; Cold, Enable Sword Beam (when not at full hearts), Sword Beam Up, and Miasma Guard&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Lower Armor - 20 Armor, Night/Sand/Snow/Climb Speed up, Less Slippy when climbing, Quietness Up, and Miasma Guard&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Cap &amp;amp; Head Armor - 20 Armor, Sword Beam Up, Attack Up, Miasma Guard&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There are a couple of things to note with this mod/armor set as well:&lt;br&gt;I had to get a bit creative in order to make some of the parts of this armor work...&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For one, ToTK armor modding does not currently have a way to have 2 different sets of physics on the same armor part. What this means for this mod is that in order to have working physics on the front sash and the cape at the same time, I had to add one of those parts to a different part of the armor and so &lt;u class="SelectedElement"&gt;the front sash's model -will- show on the lower armor, this is not a bug&lt;/u&gt; and was the only way I could make it all work together. This is the sort of thing you would only notice if wearing the lower alone or with another upper armor. As a full set, it all looks and works well as a full set.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The other note is the Gloom Hearts system. The intent was to get gloom defense as high as possible. The best way I could find to do this was by adding more gloom hearts to the gloom heart guard system however by default it normally only shows the 3. I was able to add additional hearts but only the very last heart is actually visible, shown as a 4th heart, in front of the other 3. While outside of gloom and in the light, the last 3 hearts will fill and then all the "invisible hearts" will fill as well, when it finishes, the "last" gloom heart, which is the first in the display, will fill and you are at max gloom defense. From there you can spend quite a long time in the gloom before you start to take damage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The linked video will better show how this works as well as the locations for the armor.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Design and Concept Art by Skyward_Driven&lt;br&gt;A Mod by Khazmo</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/hero_of_the_kingdom_mod_10.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Armor set</category>
      <category>Models</category>
    </item>
