      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Jul 2025 23:32:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68743e1d31611.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/687441d83c10f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/687442015f259.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6874420681d81.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6874420c01315.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68744212ba35d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68744216ab398.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;A special reshade preset I developed to pair perfectly with Hyrule: Rebeautified. For the best experience, please pair this with the Brighter Nights version (HDR effects have problems with the darker night variants). This reshade does something unique in that it adds a watercolor oil effect to the game, making it so background details are blurred. This gives the game visuals almost in line with Skyward Sword. If you wish to turn this effect off, please disable "Oilify". This reshade emphasizes art direction, vibrancy, and more aesthetically pleasing lighting. In fact, this is the reason why I developed a brighter nights version of Hyrule Rebeautified too! It can be used without the mod, but is intended to be used with Hyrule Rebeautified. Link to the mod is here:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;https://gamebanana.com/mods/605379&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;INSTALLATION: Please make sure the latest version of Reshade is installed to your emulator, and all effects are installed. If they are not, you can download the installer here and update the reshade and effects:&amp;nbsp;https://reshade.me/&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;After that, place the reshade preset in your base emulator folder where your .exe is located, NOT your mod folder. Once this is installed, everything should work properly.</description>
